column5: the morning bite today was on fire
What's the report for pine falls along with the water temp. Also what's the report for the red river
see the thread "water temp" on this Canada eh page.
Water temp in Celsius for Lake Winnipeg South Basin can be found at http://weather.gc.ca/marine/weatherC...tationID=45140
I converted it for our good American friends. I still have to for myself!

Three of us caught 64 walleye on Traverser Bay on Oct 17/13. Jigging with salted minnows. Water temp was 54F. Biggest fish was 25". the drum and perch have left the Bay. No, there's no pictures, we were too busy catching fish.
fishing has been stellar on the Red and at Pinefalls. Water temp has been around 50
water temp on Traverse Bay was 53F on Saturday Oct 19. Fishing was not near as good as it was on Oct 17. Largest walleye we caught Oct 19 was 26.75" and a bonus master angler white bass in the river.

Fishing was overall good last 5 days, 10/15 through 10/20 at Pine Falls. Temps on Sunday on the bay was 53.5.Good except for my day 1 of the tourney. Not really sure what happened there, just everything small for one day. That's fishin.
Two of us fished Oct 24 from 0830 to 1700, we caught 68 walleye, 3 northern, 2 sauger, 1 white bass. Included were one 29" walleye and three 30" walleye. It was unreal on Traverse Bay.
